      <h1 class="text-center">SLAC Fund Terms</h1>
    </div>
<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>The <strong>SLAC (Supporting Local Artists of Color) Fund</strong> supports aspiring writer/directors of color in New Mexico. Each selected filmmaker receives a support package worth <strong>$2,500</strong>, including tools, crew, fundraising help, and access to Dust Wave's community — leading to a premiere screening at <a href="https://www.guildcinema.com" target="_blank">The Guild Cinema</a> in Albuquerque.</p>

<h2>What Filmmakers Receive</h2>
<br><br>
<h3>Production Support</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Access to <strong>camera, sound, and lighting gear</strong> (as available)</li><br>
  <li>Assistance with <strong>location scouting</strong></li><br>
  <li>Access to <strong>crew</strong> from Dust Wave's network</li><br>
  <li><strong>Guidance</strong> through our Notion-based production system</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Shot lists, calendars, budget tracking, and task management</li>
</ul>

<h3>Fundraising & Budgeting</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Crowdfunding support</strong>, including:</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Campaign strategy</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Page content and video pitch guidance</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Launch & promo calendar</li><br>
  <li>Assistance organizing a <strong>local fundraising event</strong></li><br>
  <li>Support for <strong>budget creation and oversight</strong></li>
</ul>

<h3>Post-Production & Strategy</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Assistance with <strong>editing</strong>, <strong>sound</strong>, and <strong>color</strong></li><br>
  <li><strong>Festival strategy</strong>, including:</li><br>
      <li class="indent">Application timelines</li><br>
      <li class="indent">Platform suggestions</li><br>
      <li class="indent">Submission letter assistance</li><br>
  <li><strong>Marketing support</strong>, such as:</li><br>
      <li class="indent">Flyer/social media templates</li><br>
      <li class="indent">Press release help</li>
</ul>

<h3>Final Showcase & Visibility</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Guaranteed <strong>premiere screening at the Guild Cinema</strong></li><br>
  <li>Promo through Dust Wave's platforms</li><br>
  <li>Opportunity for Q&A and community celebration</li><br>
  <li>Continued exposure through Dust Wave's network</li>
</ul>
<br><br>
<h2>Eligibility</h2>
<br><br>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Applicants must:</strong></li><br>
  <li class="indent">Identify as <strong>an aspiring writer/director of color</strong></li><br>
  <li class="indent">Be based in or able to work in <strong>New Mexico</strong></li><br>
  <li class="indent">NOT be a current member of Dust Wave</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Have a <strong>short film concept</strong> (5–15 mins preferred)</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Be available to commit <strong>20 hours/week</strong> to the project</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Be open to collaboration and feedback</li>
</ul>
<br><br>
<h2>Participant Commitments</h2>
<br><br>
<ul>
  <li><strong>To receive full SLAC Fund support, filmmakers must:</strong></li><br>
  <li class="indent"><strong>Meet all deadlines</strong> in pre-pro, production, and post</li><br>
  <li class="indent"><strong>Complete all required admin tasks</strong> (budgets, call sheets, updates)</li><br>
  <li class="indent"><strong>Dedicate 20 hours per week</strong> to the project</li><br>
  <li class="indent"><strong>Honor Dust Wave values</strong> — 
    <a href="https://dustwave.xyz/about.html">see full list here</a>, including:</li><br>
      <li class="indentmore">Collaboration</li><br>
      <li class="indentmore">Mutual respect</li><br>
      <li class="indentmore">Joy in process</li><br>
      <li class="indentmore">Integrity</li><br>
      <li class="indentmore">Cultural humility</li><br>
      <li class="indentmore">Collective responsibility</li>
</ul>

<h3>Credit Requirement</h3>
<br><br>
<ul>
  <li><strong>All completed films must include the following line in the end credits:</strong></li><br>
  <li class="indent">“This film was made possible with support from the SLAC Fund”</li><br>
  <li><strong>All completed films must include the following organizations in a Special Thanks section of the credits:</strong></li><br>
  <li class="indent">Dust Wave</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Cultivating Coders</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Nusenda Credit Union</li>
</ul>

<h3>Marketing Requirement</h3>
<br><br>
<ul>
  <li><strong>All completed films will be featured on the Dust Wave website (<a href="https://dustwave.xyz">dustwave.xyz</a>).</strong></li><br>
  <li>Stills and clips from the film may be used to promote Dust Wave and Dust Wave events/projects.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Terms of Removal</h2>
<br><br>
<ul>
  <li>Support may be revoked if a participant:</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Fails to meet expectations or deadlines</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Drops below time commitment</li><br>
  <li class="indent">Acts in ways that conflict with Dust Wave's values</li>
</ul>

